## Building Tic-Tac-Toe in Vue 3

**Mental model:** One array of 9 cells plus whose turn it is. Winner, draw, and status are **derived** with `computed`. Clicks are ignored on taken cells or after the game ends.

### Step 1 — Board + turn
```vue
<script setup>
import { ref, computed } from 'vue';
const board = ref(Array(9).fill(null));
const xNext = ref(true);
</script>
```

### Step 2 — Derive the winner
```js
const winner = computed(() => {
  for (const [a, b, c] of LINES) {
    if (board.value[a] && board.value[a] === board.value[b] && board.value[a] === board.value[c]) return board.value[a];
  }
  return null;
});
```

### Step 3 — Handle a move
```js
function play(i) {
  if (board.value[i] || winner.value) return;
  board.value[i] = xNext.value ? 'X' : 'O';
  xNext.value = !xNext.value;
}
```

### Step 4 — Status + reset
```js
const draw = computed(() => !winner.value && board.value.every(Boolean));
const status = computed(() => winner.value ? `${winner.value} wins!` : draw.value ? 'Draw' : `${xNext.value ? 'X' : 'O'} to move`);
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Click taken cell | Guard on `board[i]`. |
| Play after win | Guard on `winner`. |
| Draw | Board full, no winner. |

**Interview tip:** Three `computed`s (winner/draw/status) over one board ref keep the game declarative — the board is the only writable state, everything visible is derived.

