## Building Tic-Tac-Toe in Angular

**Mental model:** One array of 9 cells plus whose turn it is. Winner, draw, and status are **derived** via getters. Clicks are ignored on taken cells or after the game ends. Classic `NgModule` setup, no `?.`/`??` (the build rejects them).

### Step 1 — Board + turn
```typescript
board: (string | null)[] = Array(9).fill(null);
xNext = true;
```

### Step 2 — Winner getter
```typescript
get winner(): string | null {
  for (const [a, b, c] of this.lines) {
    if (this.board[a] && this.board[a] === this.board[b] && this.board[a] === this.board[c]) { return this.board[a]; }
  }
  return null;
}
```

### Step 3 — Handle a move
```typescript
play(i: number): void {
  if (this.board[i] || this.winner) { return; }
  this.board[i] = this.xNext ? 'X' : 'O';
  this.xNext = !this.xNext;
}
```

### Step 4 — Status getter + reset
```typescript
get status(): string {
  if (this.winner) { return this.winner + ' wins!'; }
  if (this.board.every(Boolean)) { return 'Draw'; }
  return (this.xNext ? 'X' : 'O') + ' to move';
}
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Click taken cell | Guard on `board[i]`. |
| Play after win | Guard on `winner`. |
| Draw | Board full, no winner. |

**Interview tip:** Getters for winner/status keep the template declarative; note that change detection re-runs them after each click, so the board stays the single source of truth.

